  "text": "Following kainate-induced seizures, P-gp labeling was seen in capillary endothelial cells but not in astrocytes ( Figures 3B-3D ). Furthermore, neurons in the hippocampal CA3c/CA4 layer and the hilus of the dentate gyrus were labeled for P-gp by all three antibodies ( Figures 3B-3D ; Table 1 ). As reported recently [CITATION_1] ), double-immunofluorescencently stained sections using C219 or mdr-(Ab-1) for P-gp and an antibody against the neuronal marker NeuN confirmed the presence of P-gp in neurons, whereas no double labeling of P-gp was obtained with the astroglia marker GFAP (not illustrated). Figure 2 P-gp expression in normal rat brain determined with protocol #1 (acetone-fixed cryostat sections of snap-frozen tissue). Sections are from the hilus of the dentate gyrus (3.8 mm posterior to bregma). For P-gp labeling, the antibody mdr-(Ab-1) was used in A and F, C219 in B, D, and E, and H241 in C. D, E, and F show confocal laser micrographs with fluorescence double labeling of sections from the hilus. In D, a section was treated with a GLUT-1 marker (green) for identification of endothelial cells and with an P-gp antibody (red), resulting in colocalization of both antibodies (and thus yellow staining) in a microvessel. In E, astrocytes are stained by a GFAP-antibody (red) and P-gp-containing cells by a P-gp antibody (green), demonstrating absence of colocalization of GFAP and P-gp under the conditions of this protocol. F illustrates the (mainly nuclear) neuron marker NeuN (red) next to a microvessel stained by the P-gp-antibody (green). In A-F, immunostained endothelial cells are indicated by \"e,\" neurons by \"n,\" and astrocytes by \"a.\" Figure 3 P-gp expression with protocol #1 (acetone-fixed cryostat sections of snap-frozen tissue) in normal rat brain (A) and rat brain 24 hr after after kainate-induced status epilepticus (B-D). Sections are from the hilus of the dentate gyrus (2.3 mm posterior to bregma). For P-gp labeling, the antibody mdr-(Ab-1) was used in A and B, C219 in C, and H241 in D. P-gp-labeled capillary endothelial cells are indicated by \"e\" and neurons by \"n.\" No P-gp-labeled neurons were seen in controls. ",
